commitResults.messageTitle: Level-1. Duke can now greet, echo and say goodbye, with some formatting
Level-2 done. Changed if else to switch when checking input and removed checkExit function

commitResults.messageBody: Tasks can now be marked as done.  Only works when task to be marked is a valid number. This will be address in Level-5 error handling
ToDos, Events, Deadlines done with switches.
Automated UI regression testing now possible
Most, if not all possible errors are being handled in the current version.
Added delete function and made code neater. Changed Task array to use ArrayList.

commitResults.messageTitle: Save tasks to hard disk and load on start up
commitResults.messageBody:
Our task list is lost when Duke is exited.

Storing the task list somewhere improves Duke's usability.

Let's save our tasks in a file which we will load whenever Duke restarts.

commitResults.messageTitle: Automatically save tasks whenever task list changes
commitResults.messageBody:
The saved task list is not updated if Duke crashes.

Updating the task list automatically on change ensures saved tasks will be up-to-date even if Duke terminates prematurely.

Let's write our tasks to the file whenever the user adds one.
